summary: This is a U.S. Customs and Border Protection travel manifest for a private flight (N212JE) scheduled to depart from Paris Le Bourget (LFPB) on July 6, 2019, and arrive at Teterboro Airport (KTEB) on the same day. The manifest lists Jeffrey Edward Epstein as a passenger and indicates he was the subject of law enforcement alerts (NCIC, RIM, SE, PSE).

keyFacts: Jeffrey Epstein was scheduled to travel on a private flight (N212JE) from Paris to Teterboro on July 6, 2019.
The travel manifest was generated by U.S. Customs and Border Protection on July 5, 2019, indicating advance monitoring of his travel.
Epstein's record was flagged with multiple law enforcement alerts: NCIC, RIM, SE, and PSE.
The document is marked 'For Official Use Only / Law Enforcement Sensitive', indicating its restricted nature.
